  5→//! VVK Emplace/Vacate - Install and uninstall kit assets
  6→//!
  7→//! Full install/uninstall operations including git commits.
  8→//! Bash scripts (vvi_install.sh, vvu_uninstall.sh) are thin bootstraps
  9→//! that detect platform and exec the binary.
 10→//!
 11→//! Emplace behavior (nuclear install):
 12→//! 1. Parse burc.env, resolve paths relative to burc.env location
 13→//! 2. Verify git repo is clean
 14→//! 3. Read brand identity from parcel
 15→//! 4. Validate exact match: parcel kits == BURC_MANAGED_KITS
 16→//! 5. Delete .vvk/ and kit directories (nuclear cleanup)
 17→//! 6. Create .vvk/, copy brand file
 18→//! 7. Copy kit directories, route commands/hooks
 19→//! 8. Freshen CLAUDE.md with kit sections
 20→//! 9. Commit installation
 21→//!
 22→//! Vacate behavior (removes Claude integration, preserves kit scripts):
 23→//! 1. Parse burc.env, verify git clean
 24→//! 2. Read brand file from .vvk/ to get kit list
 25→//! 3. Remove commands and hooks from .claude/
 26→//! 4. Collapse CLAUDE.md sections to UNINSTALLED markers
 27→//! 5. Delete vvx binary from Tools/vvk/bin/
 28→//! 6. Delete brand file and .vvk/
 29→//! 7. Commit uninstallation
 30→//!
 31→//! Note: Kit directories (buk/, jjk/, etc.) are intentionally preserved.
 32→//! They contain open-source utilities usable outside Claude Code.
 33→
